# compute/{{PLATFORM}}/{{NAME}}

{{PURPOSE}}

Managed Kubernetes on {{PLATFORM}}. Exposes the standard cluster output set so downstream `helm` / `kubernetes` providers can be wired uniformly across clouds.

## Usage

```hcl
module "{{NAME}}" {
  source = "git::https://github.com/<org>/traefik-demo.git//compute/{{PLATFORM}}/{{NAME}}?ref=vX.Y.Z"

  cluster_name     = "demo"
  cluster_location = "us-east-1"
}

provider "kubernetes" {
  host                   = module.{{NAME}}.host
  cluster_ca_certificate = base64decode(module.{{NAME}}.cluster_ca_certificate)
  token                  = module.{{NAME}}.token
}
```

## Outputs

Every cluster module in `compute/` exposes the same five: `host`, `cluster_ca_certificate`, `token`, `kubeconfig`, `cluster_id`. Add cloud-specific extras (`region`, `version`, `node_pool_id`) below.

